@startuml OCR Engine Pool Pattern

title OCR Engine Pool - Thread-Safe Resource Management

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA

package "Main Thread" {
  component "MainForm" as UI
  component "ScanOrchestrator" as Orchestrator
  component "ArtifactScraper" as Scraper
}

package "Worker Threads" {
  component "Worker 1" as W1 #LightBlue
  component "Worker 2" as W2 #LightGreen
  component "Worker 3" as W3 #LightCoral
}

package "OCR Engine Pool" {
  storage "ConcurrentBag<IOcrEngine>" as Pool {
    component "Engine 1" as E1
    component "Engine 2" as E2
    component "Engine 3" as E3
    component "Engine 4" as E4
    component "Engine 5" as E5
    component "Engine 6" as E6
    component "Engine 7" as E7
    component "Engine 8" as E8
  }

  class OcrEnginePool {
    - engines : ConcurrentBag<IOcrEngine>
    - maxEngines : int = 8
    + BorrowEngine() : IOcrEngine
    + ReturnEngine(IOcrEngine) : void
    + {static} Initialize() : void
  }
}

queue "Work Queue" as Queue {
  artifact "OCRImageCollection 1" as Item1
  artifact "OCRImageCollection 2" as Item2
  artifact "OCRImageCollection 3" as Item3
  artifact "..." as More
}

UI -> Orchestrator : StartScan()
Orchestrator -> Scraper : ScanArtifactsAsync()

Scraper -> Queue : Enqueue(Item1)
Scraper -> Queue : Enqueue(Item2)
Scraper -> Queue : Enqueue(Item3)
note right: Main thread captures screenshots\nand enqueues OCR tasks

W1 -> Queue : Dequeue()
Queue --> W1 : Item1
W1 -> OcrEnginePool : BorrowEngine()
activate W1
OcrEnginePool -> E1 : TryTake()
activate E1
E1 --> W1 : Engine acquired
note right: Thread-safe via ConcurrentBag

W2 -> Queue : Dequeue()
Queue --> W2 : Item2
W2 -> OcrEnginePool : BorrowEngine()
activate W2
OcrEnginePool -> E2 : TryTake()
activate E2
E2 --> W2 : Engine acquired

W3 -> Queue : Dequeue()
Queue --> W3 : Item3
W3 -> OcrEnginePool : BorrowEngine()
activate W3
OcrEnginePool -> E3 : TryTake()
activate E3
E3 --> W3 : Engine acquired

W1 -> E1 : RecognizeAsync(image)
note right: OCR processing (1-3 seconds typical)
E1 --> W1 : OcrResult

W1 -> OcrEnginePool : ReturnEngine(E1)
OcrEnginePool -> E1 : Add()
deactivate E1
note right: Engine returned to pool\nAvailable for next task

W1 -> Queue : Dequeue()
note right: Worker immediately picks up next task

W2 -> E2 : RecognizeAsync(image)
E2 --> W2 : OcrResult
W2 -> OcrEnginePool : ReturnEngine(E2)
OcrEnginePool -> E2 : Add()
deactivate E2

W3 -> E3 : RecognizeAsync(image)
E3 --> W3 : OcrResult
W3 -> OcrEnginePool : ReturnEngine(E3)
OcrEnginePool -> E3 : Add()
deactivate E3

deactivate W1
deactivate W2
deactivate W3

note bottom of Pool
  **Pool Initialization:**

  static void Initialize()
  {
      for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++)
      {
          var engine = new TesseractEngine(
              datapath: "./tessdata",
              language: "genshin_best_eng",
              engineMode: EngineMode.Default
          );
          engines.Add(engine);
      }
  }

  **Why 8 Engines?**
  - Initialization is expensive (50-100ms per engine)
  - Pre-initialized pool avoids startup cost
  - 8 engines > 3 workers = no starvation
  - ConcurrentBag = thread-safe, lock-free
end note

note bottom of Queue
  **Thread Coordination:**

  Main Thread (Scraper):
  - Captures screenshots (fast)
  - Enqueues OCR tasks
  - Never blocks on OCR

  Worker Threads (2-3):
  - Dequeue tasks
  - Borrow engine from pool
  - Process OCR (slow)
  - Return engine
  - Repeat

  Benefits:
  - Parallel OCR processing
  - Main thread responsive
  - No thread starvation
  - Graceful degradation if OCR hangs
end note

@enduml
